1. Stacked Barcharts

Stacked barcharts include percentage answers for every answer option to a given survey question, for every student group included in the question.

Q: Quality of overall curriculum

stackedbarplot(df1bio, 'Aspect', subttextbio )

stackedbarplot(df1MH, 'Aspect', subttextmh )

stackedbarplot(df1bnb, 'Aspect', subttextbnb)

stackedbarplot(df1HPM, 'Aspect', subttextHPM)

2. Treemap Charts

Treemaps add one more level of aggregation to student’s answers, providing a visual summary of eacxh student group overall “sentiment” as reflected by their answers in the survey.

It takes a list of selected questions that have the same answer options and shows the relative answer proportions given by each group, all the given questions. Inner rectangle sizes are proportional to overall counts for each group.

A treemap example for selected questions 1 with answer options = {‘Poor’, ‘Fair’, ‘Good’, ‘Very good’, ‘Excellent’} is shown below:

# list of selected tables to include in tree aggregation:
mtx_lst_tree <- c("Quality of overall curriculum", "Quality of course content", "Relevance of course content", "Overall program quality", "Selection of online courses", "Your academic experience at Johns Hopkins", "Your student life experience at Johns Hopkins", "Your overall experience at Johns Hopkins",
   "Breadth of courses offered", "Depth of courses offered", "Quality of academic advising")


x <- c('Aspect', 'N', 'Poor', 'Fair', 'Good', 'Very good', 'Excellent')
colnames_lst_tree <- rep(list(x), length(mtx_lst_tree))

#make treemap dataframes:
dflst_treebio <- make_dflst(result_biostat, mtx_lst_tree, colnames_lst_tree, dictbio)
dflst_treebnb <- make_dflst(resultBMB, mtx_lst_tree, colnames_lst_tree, dictbnb)
dflst_treeMH <- make_dflst(result_mh, mtx_lst_tree, colnames_lst_tree, dictmh)
dflst_treeHPM <- make_dflst(result_HPM, mtx_lst_tree, colnames_lst_tree, dictHPM)

# build treemaps:
maketreemap(dflst_treebio, "Overall Graduate Student Satisfaction: Biostatistics Department")

maketreemap(dflst_treeMH, "Overall Graduate Student Satisfaction: Mental Health Department")

maketreemap(dflst_treebnb, "Overall Graduate Student Satisfaction: BMB Department")

maketreemap(dflst_treeHPM, "Overall Graduate Student Satisfaction: Health Policy Management Department")
